title: Frame, late 18th–early 19th century
description: Mirror (A) in double frame (B), the outer part of gray painted wood with carved scrollwork originating in a central wreath and terminating at the sides in pendant clusters of fruits and flowers. The inner frame with pearl and flower ornament, molded.

tombstone.epitaph: Frame, late 18th–early 19th century.Wood, painted and gilded. Gift of Anonymous Donor. 1937-45-7-b.
